üõ†Ô∏è Troubleshooting Tips
1. Terraform Plugin Issues

Problem: Required plugins are not installed.

Solution: Run terraform init to download required providers.

2. Kubernetes Cluster Not Responding

Problem: kubectl get nodes shows errors.

Solution: Run:

gcloud container clusters get-credentials demo-gke-cluster \
--zone us-central1-a --project dark-caldron-476422-v9

3. Service External IP Pending

Problem: LoadBalancer EXTERNAL-IP is <pending>.

Solution: Wait a few minutes or check firewall rules and IP quota.

4. Git Push Issues (Large Files / Secrets)

Problem: GitHub rejects push due to large files or secrets.

Solution:

rm -rf .terraform
echo ".terraform/" >> .gitignore
git filter-branch --force --index-filter \
  "git rm --cached --ignore-unmatch <secret-file>" \
  --prune-empty --tag-name-filter cat -- --all
echo "dark-caldron-476422-v9-4e5474f8e888.json" >> .gitignore


Use GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT) instead of password.

5. Terraform Destroy Errors

Ensure credentials are valid and run:

terraform destroy -var="project_id=<PROJECT_ID>" \
-var="credentials_file=<CREDENTIALS_FILE>" \
-var="region=<REGION>" \
-var="zone=<ZONE>"

6. General Tips

Always run terraform plan first to preview changes.

Never commit service account credentials or .tfstate files to GitHub.

Use .gitignore to prevent sensitive files from being tracked.
